<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=ambersmom&buddyTimeStamp=20060724&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059712&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Amber Koontz</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Amber lives at <a href='/home/?user=ambersmom'>21503 Raven Crest Circle</a>, in one of Westridge's spacious, modern homes.  She has been enjoying her view of Millsberry from atop King's Hill since she moved in on July 11, 2005.<br><br>Amber is a very friendly person, but she admits that she actually used to be quite shy!  When she first moved to Millsberry, Amber joined in on a lot of games at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> as a way of meeting people (while pursuing one of her favorite hobbies!).  Her experiment paid off, and today Amber is very proud of her shelf full of trophies and large circle of friends.  The way she went about meeting new people upon moving to Millsberry is just one example of Amber's creative thinking abilities.  She loves to find new and interesting solutions to many kinds of problems.<br><br>In her spare time, Amber likes to hang out with friends.  During the hot summer months, Amber and her friends often go to the movies at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a> and enjoy a film in the air-conditioned comfort of the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/theater.phtml">theater</a>.  Another cool summer hangout that Amber enjoys is the mall.  She can spend hours at a time browsing through the new age, pop, and punk CDs in a music store or the latest pink and violet fashions at a trendy clothing store.  Amber also spends many long summer afternoons at her best friend's house where they like to talk, listen to music, and play games.<br><br>When she has a moment to herself, Amber enjoys curling up with a good book.  Her love of reading is one of the reasons why Amber is so intelligent.  She reads as much as she can, from as wide a variety of subjects as possible.  Amber's current favorite reading topic, though, is animals.  Whether a book is fiction or nonfiction, if it's about animals, Amber will certainly want to read it!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Amber, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
